    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: March 15, 2026</p>

    <div class="highlight">
      <p>📋 <strong>Short version:</strong> QAce does not collect, store, or share any personal data. All preferences are saved locally on your device only.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
    <p>Welcome to <strong>QAce — Ace Your QA Interview</strong> ("App", "we", "our"). This Privacy Policy explains how we handle information when you use our mobile application available on iOS and Android.</p>
    <p>We are committed to protecting your privacy. QAce is designed to work without collecting any personal data.</p>

    <hr>

    <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>

    <h2>2.1 Data stored locally on your device</h2>
    <p>QAce stores the following data <strong>only on your device</strong> using local storage (AsyncStorage). This data never leaves your device and is never transmitted to our servers or any third party:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Language preference</strong> — your chosen interface language (English or Ukrainian)</li>
      <li><strong>Theme preference</strong> — dark or light mode setting</li>
      <li><strong>Quiz statistics</strong> — number of quizzes completed and your last quiz result</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2.2 Information we do NOT collect</h2>
    <p>We do not collect, store, or process:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Personal identification information (name, email, phone number)</li>
      <li>Location data</li>
      <li>Device identifiers or hardware information</li>
      <li>Payment or financial information</li>
      <li>Usage analytics or behavioral data</li>
      <li>Crash reports or diagnostic data</li>
      <li>Any data that could identify you personally</li>
    </ul>

    <hr>

    <h2>3. How We Use Information</h2>
    <p>The locally stored data is used solely to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Remember your language and theme preferences between app sessions</li>
      <li>Display your quiz progress on the home screen</li>
    </ul>
    <p>This data is never used for advertising, analytics, or any other purpose.</p>

    <hr>

    <h2>4. Data Sharing</h2>
    <p>We do not share any data with third parties because we do not collect any data that could be shared.</p>
    <p>QAce does not use:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Analytics services (Google Analytics, Firebase, etc.)</li>
      <li>Advertising networks</li>
      <li>Social media integrations</li>
      <li>Third-party tracking tools</li>
    </ul>

    <hr>

    <h2>5. Data Storage and Security</h2>
    <p>All data is stored locally on your device. We have no access to this data. If you uninstall the app, all locally stored data is permanently deleted.</p>

    <hr>

    <h2>6. Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>QAce is not directed at children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect any information from children. The app contains educational content suitable for adults preparing for professional QA engineering interviews.</p>

    <hr>

    <h2>7. Future Updates</h2>
    <p>In future versions of QAce, we may introduce features that require additional data collection, such as:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>User accounts and cloud sync</li>
      <li>In-app purchases</li>
      <li>Push notifications</li>
      <li>Analytics to improve app performance</li>
    </ul>
    <p>If we introduce such features, this Privacy Policy will be updated before the release, and you will be notified through the app.</p>

    <hr>

    <h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>Since we do not collect any personal data, there is no personal information for us to provide, correct, or delete. If you wish to remove all locally stored preferences, simply uninstall the app.</p>

    <hr>

    <h2>9. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>The current version of QAce does not integrate any third-party services.</p>

    <hr>

    <h2>10. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by updating the "Last updated" date at the top of this page. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically.</p>

